title: Egypt intensifies crackdown ahead of key U.S. decision on military aid
description: The U.S. State Department must decide by Sept. 14 whether to withhold a portion of the roughly $1.3 billion in annual military aid to Egypt over human rights concerns.

title: Whatever the fuss over Elon Musk, Starlink is utterly essential in Ukraine
description: A new biography has reignited concerns about the billionaire’s influence over the war in Ukraine, but for the country and and its military the satellite internet service that SpaceX provides is vital.

title: This summer was hotter for almost everyone in the world, study says
description: Climate change means nearly all of the world’s population experienced higher temperatures from June to August, Climate Central said.

title: China’s military seeks to exploit U.S. troops, veterans, general warns
description: A Pentagon memo obtained by The Post says Beijing is working to enhance its military capability by targeting Americans with specialized skills and training.

title: Museum makes time slot for non-White visitors — and gets right-wing backlash
description: Dortmund’s Zeche Zollern museum said it wanted to provide a “safer space” for non-White visitors to attend a colonialism exhibition.

title: ‘Brand India’ — and Modi — take center stage at G-20 summit
description: As India hosts the G-20 summit, Prime Minister Narendra Modi is putting a spotlight on his country’ s growth and vision for the world.

title: Ukraine live briefing: Russia learning from mistakes, analysts say; Musk cut Starlink amid attack by Ukraine
description: Russia has slowed Ukraine’s counteroffensive as it waits for the resolve of its Western backers to falter. But NATO says Ukraine is making gradual progress.

title: Rescue set to begin for sick American stuck deep in Turkish cave
description: Mark Dickey suffered gastrointestinal bleeding while exploring Turkey’s Morca cave, leaving him unable to climb up thousands of feet on his own.

title: How Russia learned from mistakes to slow Ukraine’s counteroffensive
description: Three months into Ukraine’s inching counteroffensive, Russian occupying forces have mostly held their positions, in large part by learning from past mistakes.

title: A yoga class in corpse pose was mistaken for a ‘ritual mass killing’
description: Police in England received a call about a possible “ritual mass killing” inside a cafe. It was a yoga class in shavasana, or corpse pose.

title: In the shadow of U.S.-China rivalry, a new world order is emerging
description: The Biden administration is trying to secure potential Asian bulwarks against China. But a fluid new global order gives “middle powers” more options than ever.
